    \begin {tikzcd}
      C(c, c)\times  Pc\ar [d, "f^*\times  Pf"']\ar [r, "\beta _c(r)_c"] & Qc\ar [d, "Qf"]\\
      C(d, c)\times  Pd\ar [r, "\beta _c(r)_{d}"'] & Qd
    \end {tikzcd}


 to commute. Tracking (1_c, p), on the top-left we have that
  Qf(\alpha _c(r, p)), while on the bottom-right we have \beta _c(r)_d(f,   Pf(p)). Meanwhile, naturality of \alpha  implies that 




